In this task, I gained hands-on experience with both coding and digital collaboration tools by
using HackerRank and Google Workspace. I created an account on HackerRank and completed
a beginner-level programming challenge, which strengthened my understanding of core
concepts of DSA such as logical thinking, problem-solving, and basic programming syntax and
its applications. The platform’s real-time feedback and scoring system helped me identify
mistakes and improve my coding approach.

As part of the collaboration task, I built a Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz using Google
Forms. The form included five well-structured questions, combining multiple-choice and short-
answer formats, focusing on topics like online safety, digital responsibility, and awareness of
common cyber risks. I also connected the form to Google Sheets to automatically collect and
organize responses, allowing easy analysis of participant answers.

Through this task, I built both a functional quiz and a coding solution, which enhanced my
practical skills. Academically, HackerRank helped me improve my programming
fundamentals and analytical thinking, which are essential for computer science subjects and
technical interviews which I will be facing in coming future for get into the tech companies as
a software engineer. Meanwhile, Google Workspace tools improved my ability to create digital
content, manage data, and collaborate efficiently with others.

Overall, this experience increased my technical confidence, digital literacy, and productivity
skills, all of which will support my academic performance and future career growth.
